# Required Pricing Flow

## 1. Load All Price Lists

Fetch:

```http
GET /price-lists
```

Store result:

```ts
allPriceLists
```

---

## 2. Load Existing Product Price Items

Fetch:

```http
GET /price-lists/items?productId={productId}
```

Store result:

```ts
productPriceItems
```

This effect should:

* depend on product ID
* refetch when product changes

---

## 3. Merge Into Matrix Rows

Create a compute effect that merges:

* all price lists
* product price items

into:

```ts
{
  id,
  priceListId,
  priceListName,
  currencyCode,
  itemId?,
  unitPrice?,
  exists: boolean,
  dirty?: boolean,
}
```

Store result:

```ts
pricingMatrixRows
```

Every price list must always produce a row.

Even missing prices should render.

